// Mermaid Library Wrapper
// Thin wrapper around the mermaid library providing initialization, SVG rendering,
// dimension extraction, validation, theme management, and reset. Sets up the DOM
// environment before importing mermaid.

A module-level flag tracks whether mermaid has been initialized. Rendering
functions initialize on first use if not already done.

FUNCTION initializeMermaid(options) -> void                                EXPORT
  IF already initialized, return immediately.
  Merge provided options with defaults (theme: "default", startOnLoad: false,
  securityLevel: "strict") and call mermaid.initialize.
  Set the initialized flag to true.
  IF initialization throws, wrap in MermaidError and rethrow.

---

FUNCTION renderToSVG(content, theme) -> string                             EXPORT
  IF not yet initialized, call initializeMermaid with the given theme.
  Re-initialize mermaid with the requested theme (handles theme switching).
  Render the diagram content using mermaid.render with id "diagram".
  Return the SVG string.
  IF rendering throws, wrap in MermaidError and rethrow.

---

FUNCTION renderWithDimensions(content, theme) -> RenderResult              EXPORT
  Call renderToSVG to get the SVG string.
  Extract width and height by inspecting the viewBox attribute first;
  fall back to width and height attributes if viewBox is absent.
  Return { svg, width, height } — omit dimensions if they are zero or absent.

---

FUNCTION validateDiagram(content) -> boolean                               EXPORT
  Return false if content is empty or whitespace.
  Check whether the trimmed content starts with a known diagram type keyword
  (graph, flowchart, sequenceDiagram, classDiagram, stateDiagram, erDiagram,
  gantt, pie, gitGraph, requirement, architecture, mindmap, timeline).
  Return true if a match is found, false otherwise.

---

FUNCTION getCurrentTheme() -> Theme                                        EXPORT
  Read the current theme from mermaid's config via mermaidAPI.getConfig.
  Return the theme string, defaulting to "default".

---

FUNCTION setTheme(theme) -> void                                           EXPORT
  Call mermaid.initialize with the new theme.
  IF it throws, wrap in MermaidError and rethrow.

---

FUNCTION reset() -> void                                                   EXPORT
  Clear the initialized flag.
  Call mermaid.contentLoaded to reset internal mermaid state; swallow any errors.

---

FUNCTION isInitializedMermaid() -> boolean                                 EXPORT
  Return the current value of the initialized flag.
